reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to set up and use
reviews.reviewText: This little guy is so cute, and it works really well. It took just a few minutes to set it up including downloading the app. It takes some tweaking to get the labels how you want them to look, but once you get the hang of it, it's really easy to format any label for any use.The app comes preloaded with several templates in different categories, plus you can design and save your own templates. You can increase or decrease the size of the font for printing, plus there are several fonts you can download. You can also add text effects such as rounded printing. You have to be careful which fonts you use for whatever you want to print, because some of them are so light they're barely readable, especially at smaller sizes.All functions are controlled through the app, including printing, and you can choose how many copies of a label you want to print at once. This comes in handy for me, as I use this label maker primarily for labeling foods for my freezer. I can just put in how many copies I want to print once I have the label like I want it (for homemade TV dinners, for example) and press print. In a few seconds it's printed say, 8, labels for a spaghetti TV dinner that I've made 8 portions of. I put a label onto each container, then into the freezer they go. I always include reheating instructions to make it easier for me to just pop the meal into the microwave.You can go to the company website and buy replacement label rolls that specifically fit this model, which is M110. There's a Mall section in the app that takes you to the website through your phone's browser, and it warns you before you go to the browser. All in all, one of the most useful purchases I've made.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars it's ok... may or may not work
reviews.reviewText: The Phomemo label printer is great when it works! I had to dig for information for a few hours, but finally figured out how to do what I needed. Wish they had a regular manual like in the old day, a pdf file with all the information in one spot, as the app is a bit clunky.The printing is fine... the machine "eats" parts of the first label every time I print a batch. Now it just started "printing" a bunch of empty labels after the first label in a batch (and even when I print a single label). It's frustrating to use, to be honest.Hope people have better luck with theirs, mine isn't working great.
Encantada com minha impressora, é simples e muito fácil de usar, baixei o aplicativo que é bem intuitivo. Zero dificuldades!

Its amazing. I can now use it to print out addresses instead of handwriting.I'm still playing with it, but a very powerful little tool for such little price.Recommend it for beginners doing labels for crafts, scrapbooking, and Canning.

Me va llegando la impresora, antes de lo previsto (Buenísimo) y en buen estado.primeras impresiones.Agradable a la vista, tiene un diseño bastante llamativo, me atrevo a decir que parece un juguete, todo menos un impresora.te bajas la app que indica el manual desde tu teléfono inteligente y configuras en menos de 10 min.la app es bastante visual y moderna, nada confusa.por ultimo y mas importante.diseñas tu etiqueta y te imprime de maravilla, rápido y sin tapujos. Me llevo mas tiempo sacarla de la caja en la que llego, que configurar y empezar a imprimir.la verdad estoy impresionado, porque vengo de usar una Zebra GC420T y a parte de carísima es una total pesadilla a la hora de imprimir etiquetas, diseñarlas, configurarla.LO RECOMIENDO TOTALMENTE!!!!

reviews.reviewText: Absolutely loved this little machine. It is potable and easy to carry and extremely quick and easy to use. I printed my wedding favour stickers for 400 favour boxes.
